# Custom Docker images

When an app needs a custom image (not upstream, or needs baked-in deps):

1. Put files in `custom_images/<image-name>/` with a `Dockerfile` (plus sources/scripts; optional README)
2. CI builds/pushes to GHCR on push to `main` when `custom_images/` changes:
   - Registry: `ghcr.io/nerddotdad/<image-name>`
   - Tags: semver (`x.y.z-<image>`), `main-<sha>`, `latest` on main
   - Workflow: `.github/workflows/build-custom-images.yml` (also manual via Actions UI)
3. Reference in HelmRelease:

```yaml
image:
  repository: ghcr.io/nerddotdad/<image-name>
  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent
  tag: "latest"  # or main-<sha> / semver
```

## Practices

- One app per image; only necessary deps; multi-stage when useful
- Document build notes in README; test locally before commit
